    {
      "id": "mnsik7ad",
      "questionNumber": 4,
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p>\n<p><b>Statement I :</b> Due to increase in van der Waals forces, the order of boiling points is $\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{I}&gt;\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{I}&gt;\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{I}$.</p>\n<p>$$ \\text { Statement II : } $$<img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 4 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mnsj9qz5/28c1450f-8461-4c6f-9c20-7f17966c98b1/b0125410-34a7-11f1-8461-75c223c4ecce/file-6y3zli1mnsj9qz6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mnsj9qz5/28c1450f-8461-4c6f-9c20-7f17966c98b1/b0125410-34a7-11f1-8461-75c223c4ecce/file-6y3zli1mnsj9qz6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: inline-block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 400px;vertical-align: middle\"></p>\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are true</p>\n",
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are false</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is true but Statement II is false</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is false but Statement II is true</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "haloalkanes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<ol start=\"6\">\n\n<li>As the hydrocarbon chain increases, effective van der waals force also increases. This results in increase in boiling point also.</li>\n\n</ol>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{I}&gt;\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{I}&gt;\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{I} . $$</p>\n<p>Para substituted chlorobenzene has greater packing than ortho substituted. Better packing leads to higher melting point. Ortho-substituted chlorobenzene has greater dipole - dipole interaction that para one which gives higher boiling point.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mo4intgo/3bb46290-82fd-4791-a9f5-d2d8200f3289/b5fc0680-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4intgp.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mo4intgo/3bb46290-82fd-4791-a9f5-d2d8200f3289/b5fc0680-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4intgp.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 4 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mo4inu8j/aedd165c-1a21-42a4-a8c8-776865893538/b6951230-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4inu8k.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mo4inu8j/aedd165c-1a21-42a4-a8c8-776865893538/b6951230-3b3e-11f1-85ec-6dd2964ee95f/file-jaoe38c1mo4inu8k.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 8th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 4 English Explanation 2\"></p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
